50|$|Intermodulation is also rarely {{desirable}} in radio, as {{it creates}} unwanted <b>spurious</b> <b>emissions,</b> {{often in the}} form of sidebands. For radio transmissions this increases the occupied bandwidth, leading to adjacent channel interference, which can reduce audio clarity or increase spectrum usage.|$|R
